Package sttrswing.model

Class Entity

Object
Entity
All Implemented Interfaces:
HasPosition, HasSymbol, Hittable, Positionable
Direct Known Subclasses:
Enterprise, Klingon, Star, Starbase
public class Entity extends Object implements Hittable, Positionable, HasSymbol
Entity is used to represent an Entity or 'thing' for want of a better term in the Game. It's x and y coordinates stored in .position are used to indicate where it is in a Quadrant.

    • adjustPosition

      public void adjustPosition(int x, int y)
      Adjust the Entity position (which is an XyPair) by a given amount for the x and y values. e.g. sample.adjustPosition(-1,0) - move left by 1 sample.adjustPosition(1,0) - move right by 1 sample.adjustPosition(0,-1) - move up by 1 sample.adjustPosition(0,1) - move down by 1 sample.adjustPosition(0,0) - don't move sample.adjustPosition(-1,-1) - move left 1 and up 1 sample.adjustPosition(1,1) - move right 1 and down 1 sample.adjustPosition(-1,1) - move left 1 and down 1 sample.adjustPosition(1,-1) - move right 1 and up 1
      Specified by:
      adjustPosition in interface Positionable
      Parameters:
      x - - amount we wish to adjust the horizontal position of this Entity by.
      y - - amount we wish to adjust the vertical position of this Entity by.
